00:02:26.409 --> 00:02:32.319
Much more intense, real intense core workout,
and also up through our back.

00:02:32.319 --> 00:02:36.450
Because as we hop, we have to stabilize up
throught the back and shoulders.

00:02:36.450 --> 00:02:40.439
Next thing we do, we turn it right around.

00:02:40.439 --> 00:02:44.599
We come up on our hands, up on our toes.

00:02:44.599 --> 00:02:46.620
We are in sort of a plank position here.

00:02:46.620 --> 00:02:53.939
And we walk it out, OK, same exact thing in
a reverse pattern that we did with our legs.

00:02:53.939 --> 00:03:00.650
Really pushing, again, working your core,
pushing with your upper body.

00:03:00.650 --> 00:03:02.700
Up against a lot of resistance

00:03:02.700 --> 00:03:13.569
You have got your triceps working, your chest,
OK, 30 seconds.

00:03:13.569 --> 00:03:16.939
Then you drop it down.

00:03:16.939 --> 00:03:21.500
Now, we are going to pull the belt towards
us, almost like a lat pull-down.

00:03:21.500 --> 00:03:28.099
So one arm walks it down, and down.

00:03:28.099 --> 00:03:29.790
